[normal]Written evidence from the [bold]Tees Valley Rural Community Council[bold] 
[normal](TIC 074)[bold]This submission is based on TVRCC’s 
[normal]strategic and 
[normal]practical involvement in rural 
[normal]transport 
[normal]and experience of operating a community transport service in East Cleveland for the past three years.
[normal]The response focusses significantly on rural
[normal] residents with additional, supported travel needs – older people, people with mobility problems, and the young.
[normal]The reasons for the higher costs of rural transport are discussed.
[normal]There is an emphasis on working with and within rural communities, partnersh
[normal]ip working with the local authorities, and working with volunteers.
[normal]The importance of some degree of subsidy to the success of transport ventures in rural areas, and innovative approaches, including the use of smaller vehicles and community car schemes, ar
[normal]e highlighted.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How do Government and local authorities identify demand for passenger transport in isolated communities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)?[bold](
[normal]This question essentially requires a 
[normal]direct 
[normal]response from local authorities
[normal].
[normal])
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young [bold]people) taken into account in determining the provision of public transport to isolated communities?[bold](
[normal]This question also requires a 
[normal]direct 
[normal]response from local authorities.
[normal])
[normal]What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges [bold]be overcome?[bold]How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to [bold]rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?[bold]What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable?[bold]&#xa0;
